Language learning requires constant practice and dedication. Here are some tips to help you on your journey:

1. Immersion - try to surround yourself with the new language as much as possible by watching TV shows, movies, or YouTube videos in the target language; 
2. Repetition - repetition is key when it comes to memorizing vocabulary, so try to review words you've learned earlier using spacing repetition software like Anki;
3. Conversation practice - find a language partner who is willing to engage in conversational practices with you on a regular basis;
4. Grammar drills - use apps like Duolingo to help you memorize grammatical rules through consistent short drills;
5. Listen to music and podcasts - enable subtitles when listening to music and podcasts in the target language; this not only helps with vocabulary expansion, but also exposure to the native accent.

Through consistent and dedicated effort, coupled with these suggestions, you will be well on your way to mastering a second language!

